POLS 3362 - Western Political Theory from the
Enlightenment
Examines the major contributions to Western political thought of
Hobbes, Locke, Rousseau, the English Utilitarians, Marx, Nietzsche,
their critics and their contemporaries with an emphasis on their
continuing influence on the way we frame and discuss political
questions.
Prerequisite: POLS 2305 and 2306.
